SUMMARY of Incident:

Initial Information:

      I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police completed this narrative, and the following summary of events is based on what I viewed on surveillance video and what was learned during a recorded interview with Kristen NAILL.  It should be considered as such, and a formal review of the interview with NAILL and the surveillance video is needed.  

      On February 10, 2023, at approximately 03:17 P.M., the reported homeowner of 334 East Baltimore St, Taneytown, MD, reported that someone was threatening to kill him and that he would shoot them.  They did not ID themselves but did advise they had a firearm.  It is believed that there was also a lot of yelling in the background, and then the phone was hung up.  A second phone call came in, during which a third party advised they heard multiple guns shots.  Please see included Google Maps for location information.  Please refer to 911 calls for the exact statements made, above is what was reported to me.    

      When Officers arrived at the scene, two white males were discovered suffering from gunshot wounds.  Both of whom were transported to the Shock Trauma, Priority One.  These subjects were identified as Michael JOINER (7/7/86) and Ted RILL (3/17/89).  EMS reports and medical reports are pending for this case.  Preliminarily, RILL was suffering from approximately three (3) gunshot wounds to the stomach, and JOINER was suffering from approximately one (1) gunshot. 

      In this case, I believe there are two parties involved.  The property owner and his fiancé, and the two adult males who drove to the property.  The property owner was identified as Michael JOINER (7/7/86), and his fiancé was identified as Kristen NAILL (6/5/89).  The male subjects who drove to the scene were Ted RILL (3/17/89) and Lester RILL (7/24/64).  NAILL would advise that Michael JOINER is the owner of the property and in control of all parts of the property.  Maryland Real Property Search would indicate the same, that Michael JOINER is the owner.  It should be noted a third person was also present during the incident who resides in the garage where JOINER and NAILL are believed to have exited prior to the incident.  This subject, reportedly JOINER's brother, was identified as Donald HOLT (6/26/1995).  Pictures and additional information are provided below.  It should be noted that Lester RILL advises that it was HOLT who shot not only Ted RILL but also Michael Joiner.  Please see Lester RILL's statement for further information.  

      When I arrived at the scene, I was able to view surveillance video from the property and observed a recording of the incident.  This was shown to me by NAILL, using her cellular phone.  While viewing the video, I observed Ted RILL and Lester RILL drive to the property and park in the rear of the property.  It should be noted that upon further inspection, I believe the location where RILL parked and the start of the assaults, was actually 336 East Baltimore Street.  If not included elsewhere, this is to show cause why a search warrant was done for the property of 334 East Baltimore Street and why I obtained a Consent to Search from 336 East Baltimore Street. 

      I observed Ted RILL exit the truck, and later Lester RILL.  It initially appears that Ted RILL was talking on his cellular phone, possibly to NAILL or JOINER.  Shortly after exiting the truck, I observed Michael JOINER and Kristen NAILL walking at a fast pace to Lester RILL and Ted RILL.  NAILL and JOINER appeared to have been coming from the garage at the rear of the property, 334 East Baltimore, prior to the incident.  As stated above, I believe they all came together off of JOINER's property, and actually on the property of 336 East Baltimore Street.  It should also be noted that based on the video and later from the recorded statement from NAILL, she and JOINER both had firearms – which they appear to have pointed towards the RILLs at the start of the incident.

      To preface the rest of this information, it should be noted that NAILL mentions having a firearm while showing me the surveillance video from 334 East Baltimore Street.  Due to this, I conducted a recorded interview with NAILL – who was provided her Miranda Rights and agreed to speak with me.  A copy of the form I read to NAILL has been included with the case file for review.  It should be noted that NAILL's hands were covered in blood, so I did not have her sign the form.  NAILL read the form with me and verbally consented to speak with me.  The following is a combination of surveillance and NAILL's statement.  The recorded interview should be reviewed for formal statements made.  The following was my interpretation of NAILL's statement and the video surveillance.     

      On the surveillance video, there appears to be an exchange of words, and then a fight is observed between NAILL and Ted RILL.  NAILL would advise during her recorded interview that the fight was over the "green" gun she had.  Ted RILL is seen taking an item from NAILL, but it should be noted that surveillance video would indicate that she positioned the item (green handgun by her admission) well within arms reach of Ted RILL - possibly in his face.  During this fight over the gun, NAILL would advise that she or RILL dropped the magazine out of the firearm, leaving one round the in the chamber.  It should be noted that while walking over to the parking pad, it appears that NAILL removes the firearm from her clothing and 'racks' the slide.  Meaning, she pulled the slide back, allowing a round from the magazine to be chambered and ready to fire by pulling the trigger.  This is supported by evidence found by MSP Crime Scene Units, who located an intact (able to be fired) round along the travel path of NAILL.    

      Ted RILL then appears to turn his attention to Michael JOINER, who appears to be aiming his handgun at Lester RILL.  I believe it is a handgun and not a knife, due to JOINER's body position, which appears to be a shooter's stance.  This can be observed by viewing the camera from the middle school.  Ted RILL's movement appears to be very quick, as I believe JOINER's attention was on Lester RILL.  Once over to JOINER, it appears that Ted RILL strikes JOINER multiple times with the firearm.  It is believed that at some point, the "green" handgun in RILL's possession goes off, striking JOINER.  According to NAILL, Michael JOINER then used his .40 Cal or .45 Cal firearm to shoot Ted RILL, now believed to be a .45 caliber handgun.  It appears that this occurred in front of the shed next to the garage, which I believe is on 334 East Baltimore Street - JOINER's property.  It should be noted that in a review of the information provided by Lester RILL, he indicates that JOINER had a knife.  As stated above, Lester RILL advises it was HOLT who shot Ted RILL and JOINER.       

      After this, both parties appear to go to opposite areas, and police arrived at the scene soon after.  It does not appear that any life-saving measures were attempted from one party to the other, but instead, members of each party attended to those struck by gunfire (in their party).  


Addition to Video:

      At some point during the initial chaos of the scene, it was reported that the "other" male was the one who shot not only Ted RILL but also accidentally shot JOINER.  This subject was identified as Donald HOLT, who is prohibited from owning or possessing firearms.  In the surveillance video, there is one point where HOLT is observed near the shed with his arm outstretched in what could be interpreted as a one-handed shooting stance.  This eyewitness account was provided to TFC Potvin by Lester RILL.  Please see TFC Potvin's report for further information, as well as Lester RILL's written statement.  Further review of this is needed, and likely a follow-up interview with Lester RILL.        

      It is important to note that both parties had young children present during the time of the incident.  This includes JOINER and NAILL's children who were on the property, as well as what was reported to me as Ted RILL's child.  I was advised by initial Troopers on the scene that they checked the residence to ensure no one was injured inside and did not find anyone injured, but added there was what appeared to be blood inside the residence.  Officers also advised me about several firearms in plain view, around the rear of the property – near the garage mentioned above.

Narrative:

      Based on the information contained in the initial report, I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division authored a search warrant for the property.  While most scenes can be processed without a search warrant, the circumstances of the incident led me to believe that a search warrant was required for 334 East Baltimore Street.  In conjunction with the search warrant, permission to search the backyard of 336 East Baltimore Street, was granted by Wayne Hamborg.  This was done as I believe part of the incident occurred on that property, specifically the parking pad.

      For the search warrant, I wrote to include the scene of the crime (backyard), the garage (where NAILL and JOINER are believed to have come from), and the residence (due to surveillance on the home and blood observed inside the home).  The primary focus of the search warrant was for any and all items that could be related to the shooting.  Another part of the reason for the search was evidence related to the cause of the incident.  During my initial investigation, several people related to the case (one being NAILL), referenced a Tamper as the cause.  Initially, I believed that she was referring to a small hand tamper; however, it was later indicated to me that it was an engine-driven Tamper.  Even with the increase in the value of the item, I did not feel this level of violence was consistent with JOINER reportedly wanting to tell the RILLs about who stole their tamper.  It should be noted that while speaking with NAILL she indicated that they had just met earlier that day about the tamper, and then they started getting threatening calls (and possibly messages) from the RILLs.  NAILL would indicate that the contact was to give a warning that the RILLs were reportedly going to "kill" them. 

      Based on the above information and the information contained in my initial report, I authored a search warrant for the property - every inch of the property.  The search warrant was subsequently signed by the Honorable Judge F. Hecker of the Circuit Court of Maryland, in Carroll County.  Please see the attached search warrant, inventory sheets, property sheets, and photographs for more information.  The search of the property was a combined effort of MSP, Taneytown Police, and Carroll County Sheriff's Office.  I have broken down the items from each section, provided below.  It should be noted that Sgt. Angermeier was the scribe for approximately all the search warrant inventories; however, I was the seized officer.

Narrative:

      On the day of the incident, these two vehicles were seized and stored at the Maryland State Police Westminster Barrack.  I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division made this request due to the nature of the incident.  Specifically, the 3500 was the vehicle that the RILLs showed up in, just prior to the shooting.  Additionally, the Spark was a vehicle that arrived at the scene just after the incident occurred.  The view of the vehicle was limited, and it was unknown if any parties involved accessed the vehicle after the incident to conceal/store items related to the case.

      Based on information contained in other supplements, on February 11, 2023, I authored two search warrants - one for each vehicle.  Once prepared, I sent them to the Honorable Judge F. Hecker of the Circuit Court of Maryland, in Carroll County - who subsequently signed them.

      In reference to the Spark, there were no weapons or contraband located.  The only thing I did was take photographs of the vehicle, which have been included in the case file for review.

      In reference to the 3500, there were no weapons located inside the vehicle.  I did observe blood on the driver's side of the vehicle, which was documented in the attached photographs.  Also located inside the vehicle was a glass smoking device in the center console, as well as a jar of Marijuana in the driver's side door pocket.  I was able to identify it as such based on my training, knowledge, and experience with the Maryland State Police.  The weight of the Marijuana is 20.2 grams and was captured on PH: P-323246.  Copies of paperwork have been included with the case file for review.

      After the search warrants were complete, the seized property was stored accordingly.  I also sent the search warrant returns and inventories back to the Honorable Judge F. Hecker, who subsequently signed the paperwork.  Copies of the paperwork have been included with the case file for review.  The owners of these vehicles were contacted, and have since picked up their vehicles.

Narrative:

      On February 14, 2023, at approximately 02:30 P.M., I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division was contacted by Kristen NAILL.  NAILL used 301-305-0767, and the call was approximately 15 minutes long.  Prior to speaking with NAILL, I did ask if her attorney said it was OK to speak with me, to which she responded yes.  The phone call was not recorded, as such, this supplement was completed to the best of my recollection.   NAILL would advise the following.   

      According to NAILL, the bag of Cocaine was actually baking soda that JOINER uses for his teeth.  I was advised several times that they did not have drugs in the home.  NAILL added that this was keeping her from seeing her children, as she has been told not to contact her children.  NAILL asked how long it would take to test it, to which I advised that it all depends on the MSP Crime Lab.  I advised NAILL at some point that this case was being reviewed by the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office, and I added that I would provide them with this information.  While speaking with NAILL, she advised that Ted RILL contacted them via phone calls only, and asked if we needed to look into the phones. In reference to the RILLs, NAILL would advise that neighbors are telling them that the RILLs are circling their property.  At one point, they were reportedly fixated on the broken window at the rear of the property.  NAILL inquired about their DVR system, adding that they are not able to view the surveillance video without it.  It should be noted that NAILL and JOINER are reportedly no longer living in Taneytown. 

      NAILL would go on to advise that HOLT's employer, a local gas station - specifically the manager Cindy - advised them that the RILLs came into the store started threatening to kill HOLT.  NAILL stated that HOLT has not been able to go back to work.  

      As stated above, NAILL inquired about the inventory sheet.  I advised NAILL that I had secured the property door, and afterward, it was discovered that the item was missing from the sheet.  I told NAILL that I thought it would be best to contact the State's Attorney's Office so that they could be advised of it.  I believe I mentioned the drugs being photographed by our crime technicians, but can not say for certain.  I reminded NAILL that we briefly discussed this at Taneytown PD after the search warrant was done, but added that I did not give her any paperwork since I wanted to review it with the State's Attorney's Office first.  NAILL would indicate that she recalled this, but no details were asked.  I just advised NAILL that I did not think it was appropriate to try and reenter the home, and added that I felt the State's Attorneys should be aware prior to any additional documentation being provided to them.  

      Towards the end of the interview, NAILL requested that I call back around approximately 04:00 P.M. when JOINER got off work.  It should be noted also, towards the end, NAILL advised me that she did not care what her lawyer thought, she was allowed to talk to me.  Per NAILL's request, I did attempt to make contact at approximately 04:30 P.M., at which time they did not pick up the call. 

      During my conversation with NAILL, I advised her that I would provide the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office, and asked that if they wanted to report the threats, they should consider writing out a formal statement and providing it to me or the State's Attorney's Office.

Narrative:

      On February 15, 2023, at approximately 10:50 A.M., I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division was contacted by Sara Brown, who was at the hospital with Ted RILL.  I was advised that they would like an update on the case if possible, as well as RILL wanted to speak with me about the incident.  It should be noted that RILL is still in the hospital and has medical equipment hooked up to him, with the potential of being released this weekend.  I advised RILL that I was going to have a meeting with the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office today, if he wanted to do the interview over the phone - which he agreed was best.  The following is a summary of the information learned and should be compared to the recorded interview for exact quotes from RILL.    

      At approximately 10:55 A.M., I started the recorded interview with RILL, to which he consented.  Even though this was a noncustodial encounter, I did advise RILL of his Miranda Rights, using the Maryland State Police Advice of Miranda Rights form.  RILL indicated that he did not have any questions about the form, and agreed to speak with me.

      According to RILL, this incident all started over an (engine-powered) tamper.  RILL stated that his uncle had a tamper stolen from one of the work vehicles, and JOINER reportedly knew who had it.  RILL advised that JOINER was the one who reached out to his father (Lester RILL), and added that they even went to the property earlier in the day.  RILL advised he thought it was weird that they had them come to the house since JOINER advised them there that it was in Waynesboro (PA).  RILL stated that JOINER wanted $500 to help get the item back, which the owner of the company was willing to pay.  It should be noted that RILL references his cousin as being the one who stole the tamper and sold it to JOINER.  Please see the related Taneytown Police Department for further information.  

      RILL would go on to advise that they arranged to meet back up at approximately 03:00 P.M. (2/10/23), adding that he felt they were invited back to the property.  According to RILL, he parked his vehicle and was standing on the property next to JOINER's.  RILL advised that three subjects were involved in the incident against himself (and Lester Rill).  RILL would indicate that he had seen at least two of them before, identified as JOINER and NAILL.  The third person RILL described was JOINER's brother, who has been identified as Donald HOLT.  According to RILL, all three suspects displayed handguns after they saw him.  RILL stated that the female (NAILL) put her gun to his head.  In response, RILL stated he swatted the gun away from NAILL, causing it to fall to the ground.  When asked, RILL advised he did not believe his fingerprints or DNA should be on the gun that NAILL was holding.  While the fight over the gun was going on, RILL advised that it was JOINER that shot him twice in the leg - which he described as just going through his muscles.  RILL stated that he ran over to JOINER and started striking him in the face with his hands.  At some point, there was a third gunshot, which struck him in the stomach area.  RILL reportedly did not know who shot him, or who shot JOINER.  RILL did advise that it could have been while he and JOINER were fighting.

      After being shot a third time, RILL advised that he backed away and ultimately collapsed near the truck he arrived in.  RILL stated that the next time he woke up, he was in the hospital.  According to RILL he is still being treated, advising that while the rounds went through his legs, the one that struck his stomach is now lodged in his back.  RILL stated that the doctors advised him it was unsafe to remove the round, adding that his back is now all black and blue.  It should be noted that the doctors described the round as (approximately) a 9mm round, which they believe is a hollow-point style round.  

      Following the interview, I sent a copy of the recorded interview to the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office.

Narrative:

Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division interviewed Kristen NAILL.  The interview with NAILL was recorded, and I have included a copy of the recording for further review.  It should be noted that this supplement should be considered a summary of the statements made by NAILL, and please refer to the recording for the exact statements made by NAILL.    

      Prior to asking NAILL any questions, I advised her of her Miranda Rights.  NAILL stated that she understood her rights, and agreed to speak with me about the case.  NAILL was polite and cooperative and indicated that she was willing to speak with me prior to the interview.  It should be noted that NAILL's hands were covered in blood, so I did not ask her to sign the form.  NAILL would advise that she had an attorney for another cause, but she did not have one for this case.  Since NAILL did not have any questions about her rights and did not request a lawyer, I continued with the interview.

      According to NAILL, Ted RILL called them advising that he was coming there to kill them.  NAILL described Ted RILL as screaming into the phone.  NAILL advised that she told Ted RILL to not come to her home.  NAILL also added that there are "no trespassing" signs on their property.  NAILL would indicate that she kept hanging up the phone, and he (Ted RILL) kept calling back.  While attempting to get her 2-year-old son into the residence, NAILL advised that they (Ted RILL and Lester RILL) pulled behind the left side of the garage.  NAILL would later advise that she was walking from the garage to the residence.  This would indicate that she had the firearm with her in the garage.  It should be noted that it could be considered the left side of the garage if looking from the rear of the residence towards the garage.  Upon further review, I believe this to be 336 East Baltimore Street.  NAILL would advise that she heard him yelling, which made her turn around and see him. 

      After seeing him (Ted RILL), NAILL stated that she told him not to come to their residence.  NAILL indicated that it was around that time that Mike (Michael JOINER) also came out of the garage.  From there, NAILL indicated that Ted RILL was "screaming and hollering", adding that he told them they did not know him and do not know what he could do.  At approximately 03:48 into the interview, NAILL advises that "he" (Ted RILL) took the gun out of her hand, but added that she was able to drop the magazine out of the gun.  NAILL would advise that one round was left in the chamber.  It should be noted that while walking over to RILL, I observed on the surveillance NAILL pulling the gun out while near the family's truck and "racking" the slide.  A live .380 round was found in that approximate area.  

      Once Ted RILL had the gun, NAILL advised that he "ran" over to "Mikey" (Michael JOINER), and started to hit him in the head with the firearm he had taken from her.  At some point during the fight between JOINER and Ted RILL, NAILL states that Ted RILL shot JOINER.  NAILL indicated that she did not think he realized he was shot right away, approximately 03:55 into the interview.  NAILL stated that after JOINER was shot, she started screaming that he had been shot and described there being blood everywhere.  In response to being shot by Ted RILL, NAILL advised that JOINER shot him back.

  • 05:15 into interview

  • 05:40 into interview

Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division was able to speak with Dustin Rill over the phone.  It should be noted that his father, Rusty Rill, confirmed that it was Dustin speaking and it was Dustin's cell phone number that was called - provided by Rusty.  The interview was recorded, and a copy has been included with the case file for review.  The following is a summary of the information learned, and the recording should be reviewed for exact statements made.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
List of Attachments:

    - Copy of recorded interview with Rusty RILL
    - Copy of generic photographs of Tamper
    - Copy of email sent about Tamper (originally sent to TPD - PFC



Location of Interview:

      Taneytown Police Department - conference room



Person Interviewed:

      RILL, Rusty 
      11/03/1969
      443-744-9129

      Owner of Rill Construction.



Narrative:

      On February 15, 2023, at approximately 05:44 P.M., I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division conducted a recorded interview with the owner of Rill Construction, Rusty Rill.  The interview was conducted at the above-listed location, and I was accompanied by Taneytown Officer, Patrolman First Class (PFC) Betcher.  It should be noted that PFC. Betcher is the lead investigator in the theft of the tamper that is now believed to be the reason for the shooting.  The Taneytown Police case number is 23-TPD-000060.  I recorded the interview with everyone's consent, and a copy has been included with the case file for review.  The following is a summary of the information learned.  Please refer to the audio recording for the exact statements made.

      As indicated at the start of the interview, I did speak with Rusty over the phone prior to the interview.  Rusty started providing details about the incident, and I advised him that I would like to have it recorded.  Rusty consented and agreed to meet me at the Taneytown Police Department.  I did not record the phone call, but I did not note any discrepancies when doing the in-person interview with Rusty.    

      During the interview, Rusty would advise that he was the owner of the tamper in question, advising that he owns Rill Construction.  Rusty does provide some identifying features of the tamper, but the most notable is the knot in the pull string for the tamper.  Rusty advised that the string was broken by an employee, and they had to tie a knot in the string to operate it.  Rusty would go on to advise that towards the end of January 2023 (maybe 1/30/23), an employee had the tamper in his Rill Construction truck - parked at his house in Taneytown.  Rusty stated that this employee contacted him on the night of the incident, advising that it had been stolen from the truck.  At the time, they did not know who the suspect(s) were but later indicated Justin Heiser and Gene Barnhouse were the suspects.  It should be noted that both subjects are related to Rusty Rill, who would advise he knows who they are and could identify their voice.  Additionally, please see the supplement on the interview with Justin Heiser for his recorded statement.  Please see attached photographs, which are generic or stock photographs of the tamper that was stolen.  Rusty would describe the tamper as approximately 150 lbs in weight, adding that it would take approximately two people to move it.  Rusty estimated the value of the tamper at approximately $3200.00 (value provided to me by TPD).  

      Rusty went on to discuss the shooting by advising that Ted Rill is a family member that works for him.  On the day of the shooting, Rusty stated that he received a call from Ted Rill advising that he knew where the stolen tamper was.  Rusty estimated the time of this call from 11:30 A.M. to Noon - on February 10, 2023.  Rusty stated that Ted Rill told him that "Harley Mike" (Michael JOINER) had the tamper Rusty, adding it was in Taneytown behind Northwest Middle School. Rusty would advise that Ted Rill did not know any details, but told Rusty that he was going to call him (Michael JOINER).  After making contact, Ted Rill reportedly advised Rusty that he (JOINER) wanted $1000 for the tamper.  Rusty then asked Ted Rill to see if JOINER would take $500 and testify against the people that he got the tamper from, or at least tell the police who he bought it from.  Rusty indicated that at least the $500 was agreed upon, based on his conversation with Ted Rill.  This led Rusty to advise Ted Rill that he needed to go to the bank to get the money, and told Ted Rill to "not do anything stupid".  Rusty indicated that he never made it to the bank, but was adamant that he would have paid the money since it was cheaper than getting a new tamper.  Rusty would advise that Ted Rill told him that they were meeting at 3 o'clock (3 P.M.).  It was around this time that Rusty learned Justin Heiser and Gene Barnhouse (family members and ex-employees), were the ones who stole the tamper - with a 3rd person (believed to be "Brandon" or Charles Brandon Rouzer).  That was the last that Ted Rill heard about it until Dustin Rill (Rusty's son) called him that afternoon and say that 'Teddy' had been shot.             

      After the fact and from other people, Rusty indicated that at some point, JOINER advised Ted Rill that the tamper was up in Waynesboro, PA, and that "you ain't F'n getting it back".  Rusty then goes into detail about what he was told by Justin Heiser's mother.  Please see Justin Heiser's recorded interview for exact statements from him.  It is important to note that according to Rusty, Heiser admitted to dropping the tamper off at JOINER's property - and into a shed.  Rusty advised he was told by Heiser that they got $300 for the tamper, but then later advised it was an "8-Ball of Cocaine" and $50 case - for a total value of $300.  Rusty went on to advise that he ran into Gene Barnhouse, who stated that JOINER asked them to get him a tamper because he wanted to do stone work in his yard.        

      In speaking with Rusty, it was learned that after the shooting, he spoke to Ted Rill.  Rusty indicated that Ted Rill and Lester Rill might have each used their phones to contact Michael Joiner.  Rusty would advise that he was told that the reason JOINER reached out to them (Lester Rill), was because Justin Heiser and Gene Barnhouse tried to kick in JOINER's door the night before - reportedly for drugs.  Rusty would indicate that it is reportedly known that JOINER sells drugs.  JOINER reportedly wanted to get them in trouble, so he contacted Rill Construction about their tamper - possibly through Gene Barnhouse.  It should be noted that Rusty does advise at this point in the interview (14:13 into the interview), that Ted Rill does "know both sides of the street.  He knows the good and the bad".  Rusty would also indicate that JOINER told them that he had them trying to kick in his door, on surveillance.  Rusty follows up by saying that neither Rill advised him of any threats against them, prior to the shooting.   

      While talking about the incident, Rusty advises that they had the dump truck because they were going to pick up the tamper.  Rusty stated that they did not have the money, adding (at 16:50 into the interview) that Ted Rill told him that they were "just going to go there and get it because they stole it".  Rusty advises that he told them not to do anything "stupid".  Another important piece learned was that at least Ted Rill used text messages (to communicate with Rusty).               

     Once the interview with Rusty was complete, Rusty called Dustin Rill, Justin Heiser, and Gene Barnhouse.  Recorded phone interviews were conducted with Dustin Rill and Justin Heiser, but Gene Barnhouse gave Rusty a bad number and could not be contacted.  It is important to note that Rusty does advise that he spoke with Heiser and Barnhouse, prior to law enforcement speaking with them - about the incident and tamper.  Rusty does advise that he knows Heiser and Barnhouse, adding that he could recognize them if they were called and that they are ex-employees.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
ATTACHMENTS:

    - MSP 67 - Joiner Clothing
    - MSP 67 - Joiner Cellphone

NARRATIVE:

    On 2/10/2023 at approximately 1530 hours, I was contacted by Cpl. Buck #6037 and advised that there was a shooting at 334 East Baltimore St, Taneytown, MD 21787. A short time later, I was requested to respond to R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center, 22 S. Greene St, Baltimore, MD 21201 to interview Michael Douglas Joiner (W/M 07/07/1986) and Ted William Rill (W/M 03/17/1986). 

    At approximately 1830 hours, I arrived at R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center. Upon my arrived I was advised by R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center medical staff that Rill was currently in the Operating Room, receiving medical treatment for his injuries. I was advised that Joiner was awake and responsive in a hospital room and wished to speak to law enforcement.

    The forthcoming interviews were recorded on a departmentally issued Sony IC Recorder. The following interviews are not a complete and exact transcription, but mere synopsis. For more clear and concise dissertation of these interviews, refer to the interview recordings attached to the case file.

    It should be noted that prior to the interview, I was only advised that Michael Douglas Joiner (W/M 07/07/1986) had contacted 9-1-1 and provided that Ted William Rill (W/M 03/17/1986) was going to respond to his residence, 334 East Baltimore Street Taneytown, MD 21787, to kill Joiner. I was also advised that Rill did respond to the residence and both Joiner and Rill sustained gun shot wounds as a result of an altercation. Due to the information provided to me before the interview, Joiner was interviewed as a victim in the incident.

    At approximately 1900 hours, I interviewed Michael Douglas Joiner (W/M 07/07/1986) in a medical room of R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center. At the time of the interview, Joiner was laying on a hospital bed, receiving medical treatment. It should be noted throughout the interview, Joiner received medical attention at various times. Joiner's mother, Lisa Kelley (W/F 04/25/1968) was also seated next to Joiner's medical bed. When asked what happened Joiner advised that approximately a week prior, a gentleman sold him a "piece of equipment", later identified as a tamper. Joiner advised that he became aware that the tamper was stolen from Rills Construction, 5109 Allendale Ln, Taneytown, MD 21787. Joiner advised that the tamper was sold to him for "a cheap price". Joiner advised he contacted a member of Rills Construction and advised that he wished to return the tamper back to the company, advising that he was aware that the owner's nephew was the one that stole the tamper. Joiner then went on to advise that he was contacted by Ted William Rill (W/M 03/17/1986), who advised him he was going to come to Joiner's residence, 334 East Baltimore Street Taneytown, MD, and kill Joiner. Joiner stated that he advised Rill, "man, I didn't do shit" adding that he bought a piece of equipment. Joiner advised that he told Rill not to come to his house. Joiner advised that he and his wife, Kristen Amber Naill (W/F 06/05/1989) were in the garage. Joiner then advised that he told Naill to take his "380" back in the house. Joiner advised that Naill walked outside and shut the door. Joiner advised that he then heard an altercation. Joiner advised that he then walked outside with his "45". Joiner advised that Rill was initially arguing and then got into a physical altercation with Naill. Joiner advised that Naill never pointed the 380 pistol at Rill. Joiner advised that Rill took the 380 pistol from Naill. Joiner advised that Rill then pointed the 380 pistol towards Joiner and shot Joiner in the above Joiner's right pectoral, between his shoulder and neck. Joiner advised that he was in pain and went down to one knee. Joiner advised that Rill then approached him and started striking him in the face with his own 380 pistol. Joiner advised that Rill tried to shoot Joiner again, providing that he heard that the pistol "clicked". Joiner stated that the pistol did not fire again because when Rill took the 380 pistol from Naill, Naill ejected the magazine from the pistol leaving only one round in the chamber. Joiner advised that due to Rill striking him in the face with the 380 pistol and due to Rill "beating" on Joiner, he feared for his life. Joiner stated he believed "this man (Rill) is going to kill me". Joiner advised while being attacked, he fired his 45 pistol twice. Joiner advised that he shot Rill center mass. Joiner advised after shooting Rill he walked away and Naill advised Joiner, that Joiner had been shot. Joiner advised that his own blood was "spraying" and getting on Naill. Joiner advised that he sat down and got a drink. Joiner advised that Rill's father was on-scene as well and stating that he was going to kill Joiner. Joiner added that his residence was equipped with video cameras and offered the video surveillance footage. Joiner advised that he worried he killed Rill. Joiner advised after shooting Rill he told parties on-scene that Rill needed an ambulance. Joiner went on to advise that the 380 pistol was a Diamondback Firearms 380 pistol that holds 7 rounds. Joiner advised when he realized everyone was safe, he through his pistol to the ground. Joiner advised a short time later law enforcement arrived, and he provided to the officers responding where his weapon was and requesting that it be cleared. Joiner provided that Rill arrived on-scene approximately 5 minutes after he originally contacted law enforcement and advising that Rill was threatening to respond to the Joiner's residence to kill Joiner. Joiner then brought up being arrested, and I advised that he was not under arrest while I was speaking with him. I later asked Joiner to elaborate on how he became aware that the tamper was stolen and Joiner responded by stating that Taneytown was a small town. Joiner then stated that Rill's cousin, who stole the tamper, was a drug addict. Joiner then provided that at the time of the shooting, his children were at the residence. I later asked Joiner to clarify who was in the garage, and he provided that he, Naill and his brother, Donald Holt, were in the garage with him prior to the altercation. While trying to get clarification about the theft of the tamper and who Joiner was advised that the tamper was stolen by, he began to fall asleep. At 1914 hours, the interview was paused to allow for Joiner to rest.

    While the interview was paused, I provided information to Cpl. Buck with the above listed information. 

    At approximately 1929 hours, the interview with Joiner resumed. I advised Joiner that a search warrant was being authored to be executed at the residence, and he asked if law enforcement was going to be entering his residence. I advised Joiner that I was unaware of what was occurring on-scene due to being at R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center for the purpose of interviews. Joiner advised that he knew Rill's mother, Vicki Lee Perish (W/F 08/19/1960), who he provided that he was aware the tamper had been stolen as well as that he had the tamper. Joiner advised that he told Perish he would get the tamper back to her. Later in the interview, Joiner provided that it is not uncommon for him to have his pistol with him, in his garage. Joiner added that given the threats by Rill, he was "definitely going to carry it", referring to his pistol. Joiner later added that he told Rill to leave his property, but given Joiner lives at a duplex, Rill advised that he wasn't on his property. I asked Joiner if anyone intervened while Rill was attacking him, and he advised "no". Joiner clarified that he was on his knee while Rill was striking him in the face with his own 380 Diamondback Firearms pistol. Joiner stated at the time of the attack he decided and thought "it's a bad idea, but I'm going to shoot him". Joiner advised that he feared that Rill was going to kill him. I asked Joiner how close Rill was when he fired the pistol at Rill, which he approximated directly on-top of Joiner. Joiner advised that when Rill shot Joiner, Rill was approximately 10 feet away. 

    At the conclusion of the interview, Cpl. Buck requested all items that Joiner was in possession of, be seized as evidence. As a result I seized the below listed items:

        (1) black/gray Samsung Galaxy Z Flip IMEI: 351070611078823
     
        (1) blue jeans with blood stains and cut damage
        (1) black belt 
        (1) black sheath
    
        (2) black socks with blood stains
    
        (1) blue Under Armour shorts
    

    I also photographed Joiner's condition, provided below:

    

    After the interview with Joiner, the above listed items were transported to my MSP vehicle, CE-209, and placed in the trunk. I then returned to R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center and made contact with medical staff. I asked what Rill's current condition was and was advised he was in critical condition as well as being in the Operating Room (OR). I was advised by R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center medical staff that Rill's mother, Vicki Lee Perish (W/F 08/19/1960), was in the waiting room for patients in the OR.

    At approximately 2003 hours, I interviewed Vicki Lee Perish (W/F 08/19/1960) in a Consultation Room, of the Waiting Room area. Perish advised that Rill works for his uncle, the owner of Rill's Construction, along with his father and other relatives. Perish provided that Justin Heiser, had stolen a concrete tamper, out of a Rill's Construction truck. Perish advised that Joiner told her he was aware that Heiser had stolen the tamper, adding if the Rill's Construction would pay him $500.00, Joiner would return the tamper. Perish advised that the owner, Rusty Rill, refused to pay for his own equipment to be returned. Perish advised that Rill then offered his uncle, Rusty Rill, that he would retrieve the tamper. Perish advised that Rill then contacted Joiner and inquired about returning the tamper, adding that it was an approximate $3,000.00 piece of equipment. Perish advised that Rill told Joiner, his uncle wouldn't pay to get his own equipment back and that Joiner advised he did not wish to get the police involved. Perish advised that Rill told Joiner that he would come to his residence to talk about it. Perish advised that Rill and his father, Lester Leroy Rill (W/M 07/24/1964), responded over to the Joiner residence at approximately 1200 hours. Perish advised that Rill and his father dropped her off at her residence and then Rill, his father and 2-year-old son headed over to the Joiner's.     After conducting the above listed interviews and seizing the above listed items, I responded to the MSP Westminster Barrack, 1100 Baltimore Blvd, Westminster, MD 21157, where I processed the evidence. All documentation and interview recordings have been provided to Cpl. Buck for his review.

This concludes my involvement with this investigation, at this time.

Narrative:

332 E Baltimore St -- Robert Maring

Dixon then looked out the window and saw the emergency vehicles parked in front of 334 E Baltimore Street. Dixon's residence does not have any cameras. No other person was home with Dixon at the time.

I did not observe any vehicles at the residence. I left a business card at the residence front door. As of February 14th, I have not received any contact from this residence. 

338 E Baltimore St -- Jennifer Tony

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: Supplement #2 CED Narrative -- Interviews with Witnesses at Taneytown PD
IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Narrative:

At approximately 1830 hours, I responded to Taneytown Police Department to conduct interviews with witnesses who had earlier been transported to this location. The below is a synopsis of these interviews and not a word for word transcription. All interviews were audibly recorded. 


Donald Holt     0639 hours - 0640 hours.
Donald Holt was seated in the interview room of Taneytown Police Department. After beginning the interview recording, Holt provided his name and date of birth. When asked about the events that unfolded earlier in the evening, Holt said "I plead the fifth" and then said he would not speak with police about the incident without an attorney present. The interview was concluded and not further questions were asked. 


Lester Rill     0646 hours - 0656 hours
I next spoke with Lester Rill, who was waiting in an office of Taneytown Police Department. Rill stated that "Biker Mike" stole a tamper from us. Mike called Rill stated that he had the stolen tool and that he should come pick it up. When Rill and his son, Teddy, got to the residence, Mike said he wanted $500 for returning it. Rill told Mike that he was not going to pay him anything to give it back. Mike pulled out a "buck knife" from his waistband, which is when his son Teddy started to strike him. Rill stated that a man then came out of the garage with a gun in his hand and fired several rounds into the ground. This man then shot at Mike and Teddy, hitting them both. When I asked Rill to describe him, Rill stated that he looked like a "little Mexican man," stating that he was about 4 feet tall with long dark hair, balding on top, and wearing a gray hoodie. However, Rill later described this subject as having short hair. Rill stated that this subject was the only one with a firearm, and that Mike, Teddy, and himself did not have any firearms. Mike's "wife" was also there, and was the "first one to run her mouth."

Rill had earlier provided a written statement at the scene, which is attached. Rill is unable to write, so he dictated his statement to his daughter, Tabitha Ware, who transcribed what he said. 


Kristen Naill     0657 hours -- 1905 hours.
Lastly, I spoke with Kristen Naill, who was waiting in the conference room of the Taneytown Police Department. Naill stated that she received a call from Teddy, who was yelling and irate and saying that he was going to come to the house. Naill told him repeatedly that he was unwelcome and that he would be trespassing if he came to the property. Naill was walking from her garage to the residence. Once she got near her vehicle, she heard Ted in her yard screaming at them. She approached Ted with a gun in her hand. Ted took the gun out of her hand. During this struggle, the magazine ejected from the firearm. Ted then used this gun to strike him in the head, then shot Mike once. Mike and Ted began to "wrestle around for a second" until Mike shot him twice. Naill did not know what kind of gun she had been holding, but described it as a "little olive green gun." Naill stated that there was someone in the truck with Teddy and a young child, approximately 6 years old. Mike's brother, Donald Holt, was also present but was not involved. There are cameras at the residence that recorded the altercation. These recordings are stored on a black MVR that is stored in Naill's bedroom on the second floor of 334 E Baltimore Street.


This concludes interviews conducted at Taneytown Police Department.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: Supplement #2 CED Narrative -- Search of Garage

Narrative:

Pursuant to a search warrant authored by Cpl. Buck, I conducted a search of the garage that is at the rear of the property at 334 E Baltimore Street, Taneytown, MD. This is a single room concrete brick structure. To the left of the entrance is a divider made of plywood. Behind this divider is a make-shift living quarter with a small bed, a refrigerator, and some clothing and miscellaneous belongings. Among these belongings, I located a wallet that contained a North Carolina Driver's License belonging to Donald William Holt (W/M; DOB 06/26/1995). In the main portion of the garage was a red and gray plastic tool cabinet. In one of the drawers of this cabinet were two handguns. The first was an unloaded gray Polymer80 9mm handgun with no S/N. The second was a red-painted Springfield XD-M handgun, loaded with one round in the chamber and a full magazine. These items were documented on an MSP form 98a, photographed by the on-scene crime scene technician, and later transported to the MSP Westminster Barrack for processing with the rest of the recovered items. I did not locate anything further of evidentiary value in the garage.

  • 02:35 
    • HEISER advises that JOINER is known around Taneytown for selling drugs, adding that he has purchased narcotics from JOINER before.  HEISER indicates that "Teddy" (Ted Rill) does not know JOINER.
  • 03:00

  • 04:15

  • 04:30
    • HEISER states that "Kristen" is his (JOINER's) girlfriend.
  • 05:00
    • HEISER indicates that Gene Barnhouse used to live in JOINER's garage, adding that "Donny" (Donald HOLT) lives in the garage too.
  • 05:40
    • HEISER states that there is a red pickup truck in the Taneytown Police Department's Impound unit, which was used to steal the tamper.
  • 06:15

  • 08:30
    • HEISER admits to being a drug addict.
  • 10:30
    • HEISER advises that JOINER sells Crack (cocaine) and heroin.  HEISER did not know where he kept the narcotics.  
  • 13:10
    • HEISER states that JOINER gave Gene Barnhouse $50 and an "8-Ball" of crack, which they subsequently split.  As stated previously, HEISER indicates that he did get high when he smoked it.  I specifically asked if he was given baking soda, to which HEISER advised, no.
      Towards the end of the interview, 14:30 into interview is when I reviewed with HEISER what was going to happen with the interview, confirming that he knew it was being recorded (he advised he did).  After reminding him that the State's Attorney's Office would be reviewing this information, I asked him if there were any changes or corrections he wanted to make to his statement.  HEISER stated, "no".  It should be noted that HEISER also advises that he would be willing to testify to the information he provided.  HEISER does advise that he has not been threatened, intimidated, or promised anything - forcing him to give me a statement.  HEISER states at the end that he just wanted to clear the air so that we would know what really happened.

Narrative:
      My assigned department patrol vehicle, G-40, has a MVR equipped and was recording at the time of the incident. My department issued BWC was operational and recording at the time of the incident. 

      On 02/10/2023, at approximately 1514 hours, I, TFC. B. Reilly #6751, responded to Taneytown Memorial Park, Carroll County, MD to help assist in the investigation of a double shooting.

     It was indicated to me that both of the gunshot wound victims, identified as Ted William Rill (2M DOB 03/17/1989) and Michael Joiner (2M DOB 7/7/1986) were being transported by ground to Memorial Park via Medic 58 and Medic 89 respectively. Once transported by ground to Memorial Park, both victims would be flown to Shock Trauma. At approximately 1544 hours, I arrived at Memorial Park and secured the park for MSP Aviation Command to land. At approximately 1603 hours, MSP Aviation Command arrived on scene. It was relayed to me by EMS personnel that Rill was being flown by Trooper 1 to Shock Trauma Priority 1. Joiner was flown by Trooper 2 to Shock Trauma Priority 2. At 1620 hours, EOC advised that both patients were flown with a Priority 1 designation. It was also relayed to me by EMS personnel that Joiner had one gun shot wound to his shoulder and Rill had three gun shot wounds, but was unclear where on Rill's body they were located. Medic 58 personnel advised that there was clothing, a wallet and phone that was left in the ambulance that was not transported with Rill to shock trauma. All of Rill's possessions that were left in Medic 58 were seized and photographs were taken of Medic 58. These photographs were uploaded to Veripic, and eventually transported to the MSP Westminster Barrack where his possessions were stored in accordance with MSP policy and procedure. EMS personnel also advised me that Joiner still had his cellphone in his possession when he was transported to Shock Trauma. At 1629 hours, all units, including MSP Aviation Command, cleared Memorial Park and I responded to the scene of the incident (334 East Baltimore Street Taneytown, MD) to assistance further in the investigation.

     Once I arrived on scene, I relayed the information that was relayed to me from EMS personnel to the primary investigator, Cpl. Buck from Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division. Additionally, I also told him that I had seized Rill's possessions, and were stored in my patrol vehicle. I remained on scene to further assist in the investigation, until I cleared and transported Rill's possessions to the MSP Westminster Barrack. The property I seized were as follows:

1. One (1) black motoria cellphone
2. One (1) brown Levis Denizen wallet belonging to Ted William Rill cont. misc. cards
3. One (1) pair of black Nike sneakers
4. One (1) pair of white socks
5. One (1) pair of black pants
6. One (1) orange t-shirt
7. One (1) pair of blue plaid boxers

     Attached to this supplement are two copies of the MSP Form 67's.

     All events occurred in Carroll County, MD.

Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division received a phone call from Kristen NAILL.  NAILL is currently incarcerated at the Carroll County Detention Center.  I did not record the phone call on my end; however, the calls are recorded through the Detention Center.  This supplement was completed to the best of my recollection, however, the recording should be requested for exact statements and comments made.  

      During the phone call, no direct information was provided about the incident.  NAILL did inquire about the reported drugs in the home, the search of the DVR, and the search of the phones.  I advised NAILL that the suspected drugs were returned as not being CDS (controlled dangerous substance).  As for the electronics, I advised NAILL that the items were in the process of being reviewed by the (MSP) Computer Crimes Unit.  I advised her that I did not have any more information at this time, but added that all information would be provided to the legal counsels involved.  

      Even though NAILL contacted me, at the end of the phone call, I advised her that she should consider working with her attorney for any inquiries.  It should be noted that I had been previously contacted by NAILL and JOINER, who both advised that they could speak with me if they wanted to.

Narrative:

      On February 15, 2023, at approximately 07:38 P.M., I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division was contacted by Michael JOINER via telephone.  Due to the nature of the case, I recorded the phone call, and JOINER was advised that the phone call was being recorded.  JOINER would advise that he was recording the phone call as well.  The recording is in two parts due to technical difficulties with the part one recording.  The following is a summary of the information learned during this phone call and is not a word-for-word transcription.  Please refer to the audio recordings for exact statements and comments made. 

      For the summary, I listed the approximate time into the interview, then who and what was said.  It should be noted that I split the summary into parts for this information as well to capture the break in the recordings.

Mills' report), which was inappropriate in his opinion.  JOINER explained that he was "highly medicated" and "passed out" four times during the interview.

  • 03:57

Part TWO
  • 00:05
    • I advised JOINER that I had to restart my recorder.  
    • Since the recorder turned off, and I had to turn it back on, I asked JOINER if recording the call was still okay.  JOINER advised that it was "safer" to do so.  JOINER states that he understands this recording and other information/evidence will be turned over to the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office.
  • 02:15
    • JOINER advises that he was the one who called 911 (before the Rills arrived on the scene).  JOINER goes into more detail about the reason for the incident.
    • It should be noted that according to JOINER, this incident was over a tool (tamper) from the Rill's company (Rill's Construction).  JOINER would advise that he just met them (Ted Rill and Lester Rill) earlier in the day.  According to JOINER, he gave them his phone number and indicated that he did not want them to come back to his property.
  • 09:00

  • 10:30
    • JOINER advises that his fiancé (NAILL) told officers that night that they did not want people inside the home.  
    • JOINER states that there was no blood inside the home.  
  • 11:30
    • JOINER states that the item (suspected narcotics - Cocaine) located inside the home, adding that it was not what we thought it was.  JOINER advised that his children were taken away because of this item.  
    • It should be noted that JOINER is referencing the suspected Cocaine found inside the home's main bedroom, which was later tested and determined NOT to contain narcotics.  
  • 14:50
    • JOINER advises that he is "so sorry a gentleman was shot.  Adding that he was worried he would not survive".  JOINER stated that he made sure medics tended to him and that anyone on the scene should be able to attest to that.  It should be noted that JOINER states that this was a traumatizing incident and described it as him defending himself.  
  • 18:00 
    • JOINER states that threats have been made against him and his family, believed to be from the RILL family.  JOINER indicates that is one of the reasons they have not returned to the property.  JOINER states he would like the DVR returned as soon as possible.  
  • 19:25
    • JOINER references the suspected drugs inside the home, which he states he knows for a fact are not drugs.  JOINER stated that what was found was actually baking soda, which his dentist told him to use for two (2) of his teeth.
    • I did advise JOINER that I request our lab expedite the testing, which I did before this phone call.  It should be noted that I did so based on statements about the suspected contraband.  
  • 23:30
    • JOINER advises that he feels he has been treated differently from the other party involved in this case.  JOINER added that the other party brought a child to the scene "in the vehicle" and did not think it was fair that CPS was not involved with them. 
  • 26:30
    • JOINER states that the property was not fully searched and that the railing on the stairs was broken.  JOINER indicated that the main bedroom was totally "destroyed."  JOINER names a few areas of the home which he did not think were searched.  JOINER stated there was no blood inside the home.  JOINER advised that when he got home, he video-recorded the property and indicated he wanted a review of body cameras.  
  • 30:00
    • JOINER checked on the status of the other person shot (Ted RILL), adding that he was not sleeping well due to his concern.  At one point, JOINER states, "I know I hurt him."  I advised JOINER that this person was still alive.    
  • 31:00
    • JOINER again touches on threats being made against him and his family, adding that they (possibly the RILLs) are circling his property.  It should be noted that JOINER advised that on the night of the incident, he was followed from the hospital to Taneytown Police Station.  
    • JOINER indicates that the neighbor at 332 East Baltimore, Rob M (unsure last name), reportedly told him (JOINER) that he saw a Rill Construction truck circling JOINER's property after the incident.  It was indicated that this vehicle briefly surveilled the property.  
      • I asked JOINER to check with Rob to see if it was OK to give me his phone number, and unless otherwise noted, JOINER did not provide his contact information.
      • It should be noted that Taneytown Police Department did open an investigation into the threats.
  • 33:45
    • JOINER advises that someone from the RILL family threatened his younger brother, who he identified as Donald HOLT.  It should be noted that JOINER does place HOLT at the scene.  JOINER would go on to advise that this unknown person went to HOLT's work and told the manager (of the Taneytown Sunoco - identified as Cindy) that when they see HOLT, they are going to "kill him on sight."  JOINER also advised that on the Taneytown Police Facebook page, there are numerous threats against them.  JOINER indicated that this information was provided to Taneytown Police Officer Leeks.  
  • 36:30
    • JOINER indicates that the owner of Rill Construction, Rusty Rill, was the one who sent Rusty Rill and Ted Rill to his property.  According to JOINER, the RILLs were told prior to them coming to the property that the tool was not at his home (the location of the shooting).  JOINER indicated he intended to help the RILLs regain this stolen tool.  JOINER was asked to provide details about how they (Ted RILL and Rusty RILL) got the property, and JOINER advised that he authored a written statement and gave it to his attorney.  
  • 37:50
    • JOINER advises that the Rills "nephew or cousin" was the one who stole the tool.  Please see the recorded interview with Justin Heiser.
    • JOINER goes on to indicate that this subject brought the item to JOINER's property and did so by stating that they did not know the tool was stolen.  JOINER stated that as soon as they found out the tool was stolen, they immediately contacted them (the Rills), adding that they "did not want any trouble."  
    • According to JOINER, when he told 'this person' about the stolen tool, they reportedly told him they did not care and were going to come there and "do bodily harm."  JOINER stated that after that, he contacted the police.
    • JOINER indicated that he spoke with Vicki (Rill or Parish), Ted RILL's mother.  JOINER does advise that the person who sold him the tamper was Justin Heiser.    
  • 39:30
    • JOINER states that the RILLs knew the tamper was stolen, adding that they originally wanted him (JOINER) to make a statement advising such; however, they "changed their minds."  
    • JOINER advises that Vicki gave her husband (Lester) and her son (Ted Rill), his (JOINER) address.
    • According to JOINER, Rusty RILL reportedly told them (Lester RILL and Ted RILL) to get the tamper back by any means necessary.  JOINER stated that was the statement said to him by Ted RILL just before Ted RILL told him (JOINER) that he was going to "kill" him.  
  • 40:27
    • JOINER does indicate there was some talk of money being returned to him, and did so by advising that he (JOINER) told them that he did not want any money back and that he did not want to be in possession of a stolen item.  It should be noted that JOINER did advise that he has a recording (surveillance) of when HEISER dropped the tool off at the JOINER property.  JOINER stated that he planned to provide that to the RILLs, since he did not want to give a statement about the tool.   
  • 41:05
    • JOINER does advise that Ted RILL and Lester RILL came to his property two times on the day of the incident.  Once in the morning, "around 12:30", adding that they (Ted and Lester) were driving around the alleyway.  JOINER states they were approached by them (Ted and Lester), at which time JOINER states he told them that when he got home, he would contact them about the tool.  JOINER advises that the tool was at his property at that time, but because of how they arrived and their aggressiveness, he did not feel it was safe to tell them it was there.  
    • JOINER would indicate there were several phone calls before the incident.  
  • ** Please review this section and prior sections.  There appears to be some contradiction about what led up to the incident.  Additionally, it is unclear if the tool was at the property when the first meeting and subsequent phone call happened.  This does continue during various parts of the interview** 
  • 45:50
    • JOINER provides his account of the events of the shooting.
      • JOINER states that he arrived home, and that he was longer than 2 hours.  This was in reference to his earlier comments that he would contact them when he got home from the store.  While out, they (RILLs) tried calling his phone several times, but the calls were unanswered.
      • After being home, while in the garage, JOINER advises that he received a call which he answered.  At that time, (believed to be) Ted RILL told him that "he was not like his uncle, and that he would come to get the tool by any means necessary."  JOINER states that he (believed to be Ted RILL) then threatened to kill him and his family.

      • In response, JOINER is reportedly told that they (believed to be Ted RILL and Lester RILL) are passing the liquor store "on 140" and that he should "have his shit ready."
      • JOINER stated that he made sure his children went into the house and wanted to make sure that his fiancé (NAILL) went inside the home as well.  JOINER went on to advise that everything "happened so quickly" and that he (Ted RILL and Lester RILL) were already sitting out back.
      • According to JOINER, he (believed to be Ted RILL) saw NAILL and "proceeded to come towards (her)."  JOINER did indicate that he did not see this but heard the yelling, so he came out of the garage.
      • JOINER advised that he did brandish a firearm and stated "Stop. Get off my property. Stop. Get off my property."  
      • JOINER states that he (Ted RILL) went after NAILL, and "took a weapon from her hands and charged me."
      • JOINER advised that he "backed up" as he did not want to "shoot" this gentleman.
      • JOINER states that he (Ted RILL) was the one who shot first, adding that after he went down, he (Ted RILL) started to beat him with the pistol.  JOINER would advise that there was "blood everywhere" and he was "very weak."  JOINER stated, "I thought I was going to die".
      • JOINER advised that due to this, he "defended himself."  JOINER does not specifically say that he shot Ted RILL but does imply that he did.  JOINER repeatedly advised that he "defended himself."  
      • JOINER went on to advise that as soon as he defended himself and he (Ted RILL) stopped assaulting him, he backed away.  JOINER stated that he did yell for someone to help him (Ted RILL).  
      • JOINER stated that the police arrived on the scene quickly and that he "threw the gun down."  It is at this time that JOINER states that he told the arriving Police that he shot him (Ted RILL) and that the firearm is "live" (meaning that there was a round in the chamber / able to be fired).  JOINER advised that he told responding units to help the gentleman around the corner (Ted RILL).  
      • JOINER states that this can all be seen on the video.
      • JOINER stated that the officer he spoke to was Officer Jesse Castellar (Taneytown PD) and Major Mitchell.   Around this time, an unknown female reportedly came onto the property and tried to start another confrontation.  JOINER advised this woman was possibly Ted RILL's fiancé or children's mother.  JOINER added that he did not know who that was at the time but found out at a later time.
      • Soon after, JOINER indicates that he was out of it and did not come to until later that evening.  JOINER would indicate that he spoke with his fiancé about the incident and reportedly saw the surveillance video.

    • JOINER goes into detail about all the things going on in his head after Ted RILL took the weapon (from NAILL) and started towards him.  JOINER stated that he wanted to defend himself before being shot but hesitated and waited because he was hopeful he would stop.  JOINER advised that he "let this man" shoot him and assault him before defending himself.  JOINER does advise that he felt that he had to defend himself because he thought he (Ted RILL) was going to kill him.

    • JOINER advised that neither of them (Ted or Lester) called them when they arrived.  It should be noted that Ted RILL appeared to be on his phone.

  • 57:40
    • JOINER indicates that NAILL only went towards Ted RILL after he proceeded toward her.  JOINER also indicates NAILL had a firearm, as he states that Ted RILL overpowered NAILL and took her gun.  JOINER states that he did not shoot Ted RILL until he had already shot him and had started hitting him with the gun.
  • 58:30
    • JOINER advises that no text messages were exchanged, indicating it was only over-the-phone contact.  It should be noted that JOINER does advise that there should be a recording of when Ted RILL and Lester RILL come to the property in the morning.  JOINER stated that the system records audio and video.  JOINER does go into detail about the cameras.

    • JOINER states that NAILL came into the room.
  • 01:05:05
    • JOINER advises that an officer destroyed a Civil War-era rifle during the course of the investigation.  JOINER states the weapon was left at the property.  JOINER was directed to provide this information to his attorney.  JOINER provides additional complaints about the search of his property.

    • JOINER was asked to provide something about the reported ongoing conflicts with the RILLS.  Unless otherwise noted, this was not done.

Narrative:

      The surveillance system examined was seized from Michael JOINER's property during the initial investigation by the authority of a search warrant (to include digital forensics examination).  Cpl Fitzgerald of the Maryland State Police completed the forensic examination of said device.  On March 31, 2023, I obtained the records/data from Cpl. Fitzgerald and subsequently provided a copy to the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office. 

      Then, on April 13, 2023, I was contacted by the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office regarding the DVR video.  In short, there was some unknown technical glitch preventing the files from opening correctly.  I also learned that the defense counsel was also having issues opening the video.  In summary, I advised the State's Attorney's Office that my understanding was that the program was supposed to generate a report which would populate hyperlinks to the various videos; however, this was not the case.  While it is unknown why this is/was happening, it was determined that the best course of action would be for me to go to work and check my copy of the files. 

      Once at the barrack, I found that I had the missing information, but it should be noted that there was some unknown issue with the hyperlinks.  Upon further review of the files, I was able to locate copies of the videos themselves.  I then made a copy of the videos and provided them to the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office, which could open the files on their computers.  Additionally, I made contact with Cpl. Fitzgerald, who advised that he would work on obtaining the video earlier in the day (on the day of the incident), and also for the times around when the tamper in question was supposedly dropped off to JOINER.  I requested the last week of January to the first week of February.  Once this information is received, it will be included in a future supplement for review.  It should be noted that this would not require the DVR system to be forensically downloaded again.  I was advised that the system was copied, and the MSP Computer Crimes Unit houses the formal copy.  If there is any change to this information, the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office will be contacted and advised - to determine the best course of action.    

      The formal review of the surveillance video is pending and will be captured in a separate supplement.

Narrative:

Camera One Review - Camera on the residence that faces the garage on the property.

    • JOINER is standing outside when an SUV arrives at the property.  JOINER walks to the driver's side of the vehicle and is only there for several seconds before the video pulls away.

      On June 1, 2023, I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division reviewed this case with the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office - ASA S. Johnson and ASA A. Kuhns.  While reviewing, the following came up as needed for the case.  Under each bullet point, I put a subsequent bullet point with my efforts.
  • Ted RILL's cell phone passcode for Cellebrite and Axiom programs to access his phone.

    • Cpl. Fitzgerald and I briefly spoke about this matter.  I was advised that when he returns to work, he will review the files and advise accordingly.    
  • Get Subscriber information for the 717 number that JOINER was messaging.
    • On June 9, 2023, I contacted the Carroll County State's Attorney's Office about this matter and spoke with a legal assistant.  I provided them with the information needed for this phone, which at this time, is subscriber information.
  • Follow-up with Crime Lab on the testing of firearms and related items.
    • As of June 30, 2023, the items are still being processed.
  • Review the surveillance video to try and see when the tamper left the property.
    • On June 8, 2023, I contacted the Maryland Coordinated and Analysis Center (MCAC) about arranging an analyst team to review the surveillance video in an attempt to see when the tamper left JOINER's property.  
 

Additional Information - ENHANCED VIDEO FROM MAGLOCLEN

      On June 6, 2023, I received the enhanced videos from MAGLOCLEN - provided by N. Kagel.  In the file, there were copies of the video and still images.  I was advised to view the zoomed-in video of the incident (file name: "zoomX2-bc-slowdown 80 Percent"), as well as a picture of JOINER firing his gun three times (file name: "Clip of Suspect gun firing during fight").  The first video mentioned (file name: "zoomX2-bc-slowdown 80 Percent") shows the entire incident from when the RILLs showed up at the property until after the shooting.  Additionally, in the first video (file name: "zoomX2-bc-slowdown 80 Percent"), at approximately 01:56 into the video, I believe the first gunshot can be seen.  This is the firearm Ted RILL took from NAILL. The second video (file name: "Clip of Suspect gun firing during fight") is zoomed-in as well and shows JOINER firing three times. I viewed the video and was able to observe what appears to be three flashes from the gun JOINER is holding.  While viewing the second video, I believe the first shot is at approximately 4 seconds into the video, the second shot is approximately 8 seconds into the video, and the third shot is approximately 9 seconds into the video. 

      For the "shots" I mentioned above, when the video is zoomed in and slowed down, there appears to be a flash from the gun's muzzle.  This flash can be described as a yellowish-orange flash, only visible for a fraction of a second.
